# kit-manifest.in — curation allowlist for scripts/export-kit.sh (UltraMemory Agent Kit).
#
# EXPLICIT allowlist — NEVER a wildcard. Only files listed here are exported from the private
# ~/.claude harness source of truth into agent-kit/. Each line: <src-under-~/.claude>|<dest-under-agent-kit>
# Lines starting with '#' and blank lines are ignored. These files are the verbatim-clean core
# (P2-1 grounding: 0 personal paths, 0 secrets, 0 business refs) and are copied byte-for-byte;
# export records both the dest sha256 and the live-source sha256 so `--check` can detect drift.
#
# NOT listed here (hand-curated in-repo, NOT machine-copied — they need real rewording, so a raw
# copy would re-introduce private references; verified instead by the gate's deny-scan + presence
# checks): agent-kit/skills/swarm/SKILL.md (generic rewrite of the parallel-fan-out pattern) and
# agent-kit/skills/playwright-human-mode/SKILL.md (our Playwright Human Vision Control skill,
# adapted from ccpb-playwright-human-mode). If the private originals change, re-curate those by hand.

# ── harness skills (methodology) ──
skills/harness/SKILL.md|skills/harness/SKILL.md
skills/checklist-bound-execution/SKILL.md|skills/checklist-bound-execution/SKILL.md
skills/checklist-bound-execution/references/workflow-template.js|skills/checklist-bound-execution/references/workflow-template.js
skills/checklist-bound-execution/references/schemas.md|skills/checklist-bound-execution/references/schemas.md
skills/checklist-bound-execution/references/checklist-format.md|skills/checklist-bound-execution/references/checklist-format.md
skills/atomic-level-checklist-md-confirm-approval-needed/SKILL.md|skills/atomic-level-checklist-md-confirm-approval-needed/SKILL.md
skills/research/SKILL.md|skills/research/SKILL.md

# ── harness subagents ──
agents/checklist-worker.md|agents/checklist-worker.md
agents/checklist-verifier.md|agents/checklist-verifier.md

# ── harness hooks ──
hooks/harness-gate.sh|hooks/harness-gate.sh
hooks/harness-reminder.sh|hooks/harness-reminder.sh
